Game and Application Academy Turkish subtitles I am in the 3rd week of the 1st part of the Google Project Management training. I want to summarize the notes of about 2 weeks in a few days.
I had taken this training before, but because it was 100% English, I could not reach the deadline and I could not complete the training :D

My notes:
Project management is the use of knowledge, skills, tools, and techniques to meet project requirements and achieve desired results.

Project management is important to businesses because it helps ensure that a project delivers expected results without exceeding both schedule and budget.

Actually, we are all small project managers.
-Some of the skills we use to survive but are unaware of form the basis of project management. These;
*Planning and organization
*Task management
* Budgeting and controlling costs
I would like to mention how we are currently using them. Lets move forward with an example.

Lets imagine you want to buy a gift for a friend;
Planning: First of all, you need to plan when you will buy it, where and how you will buy it.
If you are going to buy over the internet, you should calculate the shipping time and plan the delivery on the day you want.

Task management: If you are going to take it with several people, a similar skill, management, comes into play.
Collecting the gifts that everyone has researched beforehand, making a decision, determining the person to order...
In the same way, if you are going to go and get the gift physically, tasks such as determining the gift, going to the person in charge, making the gift package, and the distribution of these tasks.

Budget: Determining a common segment for the gift, collecting the share from everyone.

We can give many examples like this. We use these skills in the most basic areas of our lives.
In this training, I will be aware of these skills we have and learn how we can use them in the field of project management.